{"article_id":"sKs7pnpBnf9jrrRv","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Senate leaders on Tuesday canceled plans","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"to vote on an Obamacare repeal this week ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"marking a third straight failure for Majority Leader Mitch McConnell and fellow Republicans","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"who have been unable to fulfill their campaign promise .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"Facing too many defections ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Mr. McConnell concluded","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"it didn ' t make sense to move forward ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"and said","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"the chamber will now turn to other business such as a massive tax code overhaul .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"The failure leaves Obamacare intact ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"and Democrats begged the GOP to try for bipartisan fixes","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"to prop up the struggling law .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"The Republican chairman of the health committee said","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"he ' ll try to restart negotiations .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Most in the GOP , though , were cool on the idea ,","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"the law is hopelessly flawed .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"\" I think","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"there are a number of them","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that are going to be very hesitant to try and put more money into a system","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"that","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"they are convinced","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"is going south , \"","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"said Sen. Mike Rounds , South Dakota Republican .","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"Without action , it will be up to President Trump to decide how aggressively to support the law","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"as signups for 2018 begin .","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"Republicans had been racing an end-of-month deadline","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"to approve a repeal bill under the 2017 budget ,","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"which allowed them to avoid a Democratic filibuster .","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"Some in the GOP insisted","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"they can try again ,","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"either by writing a 2018 budget","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"to accommodate repeal ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"or including it in the 2019 budget due early next year .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"But the 2018 budget is already being eyed to push through a tax reform package ,","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"and some Republicans were wary of loading it down with several big lifts .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"\" The problem is ,","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"I don ' t know","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"that we can keep them separate ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"just to be frank , \"","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"Rep. Mark Meadows , North Carolina Republican and chairman of the archconservative House Freedom Caucus , told reporters at a Conversations with Conservatives event","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"moderated by the Heritage Foundation .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"Rep. Thomas Massie , though , said","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"Democrats packed multiple issues into the budget","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"they used","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"to help pass the Affordable Care Act originally ,","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"and said","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"it could be done for repeal .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"\" You could absolutely do two things in one , \"","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"the Kentucky Republican said .","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"\" It ' s not dead on September 30th .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"Like many things here , it ' s a fake deadline . \"","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"The House passed an Obamacare repeal bill in May ,","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"but the Senate has now failed three times .","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"This latest attempt came on a bill from Sens . Lindsey Graham of South Carolina and Bill Cassidy of Louisiana .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"Under the plan , money","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"that funded Obamacare ' s expansion of Medicaid","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"and subsidized many of the people","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"who bought plans on its exchanges","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"would be pooled together","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"and siphoned back to the states .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"Yet Sen. Susan Collins of Maine late Monday said","depth":5},{"id":62,"text":"she opposed the plan ,","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"citing cuts to Medicaid coverage and estimates","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"that millions would lose coverage .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Republican Sens . Rand Paul of Kentucky and John McCain of Arizona had already defected ,","depth":4},{"id":66,"text":"forcing sponsors to admit","depth":5},{"id":67,"text":"they ' d run out of time this week .","depth":5},{"id":68,"text":"Liberal activists cheered the GOP ' s failure ,","depth":4},{"id":69,"text":"while Democrats pleaded for a new start","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"to rescue the law .","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"\" Instead of trying to cut health care ,","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"we Democrats are ready , willing and eager to work","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"to improve our health care system , \"","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"said Senate Minority Leader Charles E. Schumer .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"health committee Chairman Lamar Alexander and Sen. Patty Murray , the ranking Democrat , were \" very close to an agreement . \"","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"\" We ' re coming back to this after taxes , \"","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"Mr. Graham insisted .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"\" We ' re going to take this show on the road . \"","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"In recent days , he ' d said","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"if repeal failed now ,","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"he would demand","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"it be part of the 2018 budget ,","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"and wouldn ' t support a blueprint","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"without it .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"By Tuesday , though , his stance appeared to soften .","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"\" I ' ve been told by people","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"it makes it extremely complicated ,","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"and what I want to do is take health care up in the most advantageous way ,","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"to understand what we ' re doing , \"","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"Sen. Ron Johnson , Wisconsin Republican , said Tuesday","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"it sounds like GOP leadership might have already ruled out fusing the two issues in the 2018 budget ,","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"but that he ' d still like to try to include health care .","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"\" I have not ruled that out","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"-","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"I want to talk to leadership , \"","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"\" But I sure don ' t want to jeopardize tax reform , either . \"","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"\" Listen ,","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"I ' m [ a ] pretty flexible guy , \"","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"he said","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"when asked about using the 2019 budget .","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"\" I ' ll accept reality .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"I don ' t particularly like the current reality ,","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"but it is what it is . \"","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":215,"left":159,"right":214,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":133,"right":158,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":116,"right":132,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":111,"right":115,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":111,"left":109,"right":110,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"par